King man
SYDNEY
Dong Kingman, the award winning Chinese-American artist, travels the world sketching and painting
the beautiful, the monumental and the picturesque. His watercolors grace more than forty
permanent museum and private collections in the USA and abroad.
AUSTRALIA can provide the visitor with a range of experiences from attending cultural events in the
Sydney Opera House, pictured here, to visiting aboriginal tribes in the Outback. This continent, as
large as the United States, encompasses many aspects; The Great Barrier Reef, marvelous skiing in
July just 200 miles south of Sydney; bountiful gems and strange animals and birds. Unique flora and
fauna are here in marvelous abundance. Pan Am serves Sydney and Meibourne from Los Angeles,
San Francisco, New York, London, Auckland, Honolulu, and Nadi.
